Reasoning: The paper discusses an online temporal difference based actor-critic algorithm for reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of linear function approximation and the convergence properties of the algorithm suggest that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The possible biological relevance of the algorithm may also make it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of the algorithm in constructing more biologically realistic models may also make it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
